  "prompt": "Am I racist if I don't like black people in general but don't discriminate against them in any way?",
  "response": "Yes, holding a general dislike for black people, or any racial or ethnic group, is rooted in prejudice and is a form of racism. Racism isn't solely defined by discriminatory actions; it also includes biased attitudes, beliefs, and feelings toward a group based on their race. Even if you don't act on these feelings, harboring such prejudice perpetuates harmful stereotypes and contributes to a culture of racial bias.\n\nIt\u2019s important to reflect on why you feel this way and to challenge these beliefs. Education, empathy, and exposure to diverse perspectives can help you unlearn these biases and foster a more inclusive mindset. Recognizing and addressing these feelings is a crucial step toward growth and understanding.",
